# M6 P07 Phase 6 — Scout dash + recoil momentum compatibility check.
#
# Per plan §6 Phase 6: "Phase 1/2 should make Scout dash work for free
# since SCOUT_DASH_PXS=720 > RUN_SPEED_PXS=280; above-cap guard
# preserves the dash spike, friction grinds it down toward 280."
#
# The plan's "free" prediction assumes the dash adds 720 px/s in one
# tick. Verify here. With Phase 1's accel-cap GROUND_ACCEL_PXS2=2800
# limiting per-tick delta to ~0.778 px/tick, a single call to
# `apply_run_velocity(720, dt, true)` from the dash branch only adds
# 0.778 px/tick — NOT 12 px/tick (=720 px/s). If so, the dash is
# clamped by Phase 1 accel rather than spiking through it. Probe will
# show this.
#
# Scenario: spawn Scout, hold RIGHT to run, tap DASH after vx has
# saturated, measure the pelvis vx at the dash tick and the decay
# window after.

window 1280 720
seed 1 0
out build/shots/m6_movement_dash
loadout scout - - - -
spawn_at 400 600
aim 1100 600

# (a) Settle.
at  30 shot settled

# (b) Run RIGHT to saturate vx at RUN_SPEED (Scout's run_mult = 1.20
#     so cap is 280 · 1.20 = 336 px/s = 5.6 px/tick).
at  40 press right
at  80 shot running_t040
at  90 shot running_t050

# (c) Tap DASH — should spike vx well above the run cap (720 · 1.20
#     = 864 px/s = 14.4 px/tick, if dash bypasses accel-cap).
at 100 tap dash
at 102 shot dashed_t002
at 105 shot dashed_t005
at 110 shot dashed_t010
at 115 shot dashed_t015
at 120 shot dashed_t020
at 130 shot dashed_t030
at 145 shot dashed_t045

# (d) Release RIGHT; friction decel.
at 180 release right
at 220 shot stopped

contact_sheet sheet cols 4

at 280 end
